{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "title": "Live-role → authorization-archetype map (reconciliation)",
  "description": "Bridges the live backend/config/rbac.config.js role model (46 granular roles across 6 levels) to the 9 canonical authorization archetypes in role-permissions.seed.json. Two-axis model: archetype = FUNCTION (which permission family in the matrix); scope/seniority = WHERE + maker-vs-checker. The matrix is authored per archetype; each live role resolves its grants = archetype grants ∩ scope, with approver-capable seniority unlocking the *:approve permissions. Do NOT flatten 46→9: the granular roles carry meaningful specialty (SLP/OT/PT), seniority (officer/manager), and reporting distinctions. archetype=NON_MATRIX = outside the staff-admin permission matrix (external / transport-ops).",
